WPK's Birthday Marked in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 27 (KCNA) -- Round-table talks were held in the Czech Republic and Uganda and a seminar took place in Egypt on Sept. 20 and 21 on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea. 
 Vice-Chairman of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Bohemia and Moravia Vaclav Exner said at the round-table talks that the Songun politics giving priority to the army in carrying out the cause of socialism is a unique Korean-style political mode under socialism the validity and vitality of which have been fully displayed in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the round-table talks held by the Kampala Committee of the Ugandan National Movement referred to the outstanding leadership ability of Kim Jong Il, adding that all the successes the army and people of the DPRK have achieved in their efforts to defend their country and build a great prosperous powerful nation are the brilliant fruition of his distinguished leadership art. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chairman of the Egyptian Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea Yehia Jakariya Khairallah said in his report titled "Six decades-long history of the WPK shining with victory and glory" delivered at the seminar that the WPK is leading to victory the struggle of the Korean people to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation, meeting all the challenges of the imperialists under the banner of the Songun revolution provided by Kim Jong Il.

U.S. Human Rights Offensive against DPRK Blasted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 27 (KCNA) -- The U.S. is citing not only the nuclear issue but the "human rights issue" for escalating its moves to stifle the DPRK. This comes under fire by a signed commentary of Rodong Sinmun today. In recent days alone senior U.S. officials took issue with the DPRK over the non-existent "human rights issue," the commentary notes, and goes on:
 The U.S. diplomatic boss blustered that the newly appointed "envoy for the human rights issue in north Korea" would opt for cooperating with other countries to "improve humanitarianism and human rights performance in north Korea". How ridiculous and arrogant these remarks are. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the ulterior motive of the U.S. to step up its policy of pressure, sanctions and military blackmail towards the DPRK by peddling not only the nuclear issue on the Korean Peninsula but the "human rights issue" and a variety of other fictions and, furthermore, start armed invasion of the DPRK under the pretext of "spreading democracy." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The anti-DPRK "human rights" offensive escalated by the U.S. since the appointment of the above-mentioned envoy will get it nowhere. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Should the U.S. step up its hostile policy towards the DPRK over the nuclear issue as well as over its non-existent "human rights issue" as now, the DPRK-U.S. ties would further deteriorate. 
 The U.S. promised to respect the sovereignty of the DPRK and coexist with it in peace at the recent six-way talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The U.S. would be well advised to drop its foolish attempt to bring down the socialist system in the DPRK under the absurd pretext of the "human rights issue" and opt for building confidence with the latter.

Successes Made in Light Industry
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 27 (KCNA) -- Signal achievements have been made in the sector of light industry of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, in hearty response to the joint slogans issued by the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea on the occasion of its 60th birthday.
 Silk mills are standing in the van of the upswing in the production.
 The Pakchon and Nyongbyon Silk Mills have effected a technical innovation to solve issues arising in silk production including raising the quality of printed cloth of new patterns. They are now carrying out their daily quotas for the production of quality shirting, velvet and other fabrics for Korean clothes at more than 130 percent.
 The Pyongyang, Hamhung and other silk-reeling mills have modernized the outmoded facilities and production processes, thus improving the quality of their products and expanding production successes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Innovations have been reported from the Sinuiju, Wonsan, Sariwon and other footwear factories across the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The technicians and employees of the Ryuwon Footwear Factory have launched a drive to increase production, with the result that they have doubled their monthly production with the existing equipment and manpower. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those of the Pyongyang Shoes Factory have introduced over ten new models of shoes and made a breakthrough in an increased production.
